    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with the infield and outfield anchored by three high-efficiency starts: **Trea Turner** (64.61), **Kyle Schwarber** (63.64), and **Colt Keith** (63.01). **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** benefit immensely from a favorable encounter with Edward Cabrera, compounded by wind blowing out at the park, which maximizes their power and run-scoring potential. **Colt Keith** represents the premier MI play today; the optimizer favors his spot in the #3 hole against Brandon Sproat, where his platoon advantage and strong base projection allow him to clear the 60-point threshold comfortably. These three are our primary engines for offensive output as we navigate a day where many other starters are suppressed by tough matchups against top-tier arms.\n\nDespite decent base projections, several rostered players occupy the \"marginal\" territory between 40 and 60 points, necessitating caution. **Caleb Durbin** (52.35) remains the most viable depth option, though he lacks the high-end platoon upside of the top trio. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (41.99) and **Hyeseong Kim** (41.34) are high-risk plays today; while **Hyeseong Kim** carries a slight boost for potential stolen base opportunities against a slow pitcher delivery, both are heavily penalized by their low position in the batting order and the presence of elite opposing catchers with sub-2.0s pop times, which will likely suppress their stolen base success rates. **Carson Benge** (38.70) was the closest exclusion from the active lineup; his inability to crack the 40-point floor is primarily due to a poor park factor and a daunting matchup against Joe Ryan, making him a bench stash until more favorable conditions arise.\n\nWe continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich**, who remains on the IL, while **Yordan Alvarez** and **Junior Caminero** are currently unavailable due to team off-days. With **Gary Sanchez**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Josh Smith**, and **Jerar Encarnacion** all teetering near the 40-point floor, our daily game cap management is critical. We are prepared to pivot to the depth of **Victor Scott II**, **Zac Veen**, **Luke Raley**, **Lars Nootbaar**, or **Luis Pena** should any of our \"Lineup Pending\" designations shift toward sub-optimal batting spots or if late-breaking weather alerts materialize. **Kazuma Okamoto** remains in the wings, and we will keep a close watch on the official lineups to ensure our efficiency remains optimized for a competitive 5x5 Roto push.",
